        <bioghist id="ref14">
            <head>Historical/Biographical Note</head>
            <p>John Penley is a photographer and activist for some thrity yeras and has been associated numerous causes, including AIDs activism, the Squatters' Rights movement in New York City's East Village and Lower East Side, the rights of homeless people, and others. Penley's current photo blog can be found at: 
                <extref ns2:actuate="onRequest" ns2:show="new" ns2:title="JPenleyPixCom" ns2:href="Penley's current photo blog can be found at: http://jpenleypixcom.blogspot.com/">http://jpenleypixcom.blogspot.com/</extref></p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection contains magazine and newspaper clippings thatinclude Penley's photographs or are related to his photographic and journalistic interests, leaflets and handbills (including some original artwork) concerning the squatters rights movement. Legal documents from Penley's suit against the New York City Police Department and then Mayor Edward Koch relating to Penley's 1987 arrest (at a rally he organized ot register homeless people to vote), are also included, as are Freedom of Information Act documents and Penley's 1991 New York City Police Department press pass. There is also also a file of legal documents relating to Penley's 1982 arrest and sentencing for trespassing at the Savannah River nuclear power plant in South Carolina, as part of an anti-nuclear movement protest. AIDS activism in particular is extensively documented in a related collection also held by the Library, the unprocessed John Penley Photograph Collection (Photos 268), consisting of eleven boxes containing slides, 35mm negatives, prints in varying sizes, contact sheets, mostly in color, that document Act Up, Housing Works, needle exchange and other harm reduction activity, and that also include coverage of homeless groups, other issues and organizations, and notable historic figures pertaining thereto. Some of Penley's photography was done on a freelance basis for the New York Times. Penley's current photo blog can be found at: 
                <extref ns2:actuate="onRequest" ns2:show="new" ns2:title="JPenleyPixCom" ns2:href="http://jpenleypixcom.blogspot.com/">http://jpenleypixcom.blogspot.com/</extref></p>
            <p>PLEASE DIRECT FURTHER INQUIRIES TO: peter.filardo@nyu.edu</p>
        </scopecontent>
